From 6c1b5be0e9b6030c44066ad19ffb89df551aae9d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Vega Port <vega@milkv.local>
Date: Sun, 24 May 2026 21:53:04 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] board: fisilink: add Milk-V Vega (FSL91030M) support

The Milk-V Vega is a small RISC-V SBC built around the Fudan
Microelectronics FSL91030M switch SoC (Nuclei UX608 core, RV64GC).

Boot chain:
 freeloader (boot ROM stage in SPI NOR) -> OpenSBI -> U-Boot (this) -> Linux

By the time U-Boot runs, freeloader has brought up DDR, caches, and the
console UART; OpenSBI has handed off the FDT in a1. There is therefore
almost no board code: just the linker-required board_init stub.

Hardware U-Boot actually drives at this stage:
 - SiFive-compatible UART  (drivers/serial/serial_sifive.c)
 - SiFive-compatible SPI   (drivers/spi/spi-sifive.c) -> SPI NAND
 - MTD/SPI-NAND for kernel loading

Everything else (clocks, reset, partition table, console settings,
bootargs) comes from the device tree, so the defconfig stays tiny.
